18
00:00:12,415 --> 00:00:15,415
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:17,439 --> 00:00:19,482
<i>Cause of death unknown!</i>

20
00:00:19,566 --> 00:00:22,027
<i>Kaminoan Doctor Nala Se was unable</i>

21
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:25,238
<i>to find the cause of an illness
in Clone Trooper Tup.</i>

22
00:00:25,322 --> 00:00:27,866
<i>In a desperate attempt
to save his friend's life,</i>

23
00:00:27,949 --> 00:00:30,869
<i>Fives located and removed a tumor
from Tup's brain</i>

24
00:00:30,952 --> 00:00:33,830
<i>with the help of medical droid AZI-3.</i>

25
00:00:33,955 --> 00:00:36,958
<i>Immediately following the procedure,
Tup died,</i>

26
00:00:37,042 --> 00:00:39,794
<i>and Fives was placed under arrest.</i>

27
00:00:40,086 --> 00:00:43,465
<i>Now, the tumor is the only hope
to finding answers</i>

28
00:00:43,548 --> 00:00:45,717
<i>for Tup's mysterious illness.</i>

29
00:00:59,105 --> 00:01:01,983
General, what did the Chancellor say?

30
00:01:02,067 --> 00:01:04,778
Supreme Chancellor Palpatine
wants the tumor

31
00:01:04,861 --> 00:01:06,529
and all of the intel gathered

32
00:01:06,613 --> 00:01:10,075
sent to the Grand Republic
Medical Facility on Coruscant.

33
00:01:10,158 --> 00:01:13,203
So, then I'll be going
to Coruscant as well?

34
00:01:13,286 --> 00:01:16,248
You were not a part
of the Chancellor's request.

35
00:01:17,249 --> 00:01:18,750
I'm sorry, Fives,

36
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:22,671
but this is a matter best left
to the medical professionals.

37
00:01:22,754 --> 00:01:25,382
There is still so much we do not know.

38
00:01:30,428 --> 00:01:32,264
Perhaps we would know more

39
00:01:32,347 --> 00:01:35,433
if this clone had not taken matters
into his own hands.

40
00:01:35,517 --> 00:01:37,894
Listen ! I was trying to save my friend!

41
00:01:37,978 --> 00:01:42,774
And yet perhaps by removing
this tumor, it was you who killed him.

42
00:01:42,857 --> 00:01:44,276
What do you care?

43
00:01:44,359 --> 00:01:47,112
You were going to kill him anyway,
and dissect him, too.

44
00:01:47,195 --> 00:01:49,322
He's a soldier. He deserves better!

45
00:01:49,948 --> 00:01:51,908
Stand down, Fives!

46
00:01:51,992 --> 00:01:55,203
Doctor, there is no proof of your claim.

47
00:01:57,539 --> 00:02:02,585
I want this specimen and all the data
prepared for transit to the Jedi Temple.

48
00:02:03,795 --> 00:02:05,964
The Chancellor said the tumor and data

49
00:02:06,047 --> 00:02:09,801
was to be sent directly
to the Medical Facility on Coruscant,

50
00:02:09,884 --> 00:02:11,594
not the Jedi Temple.

51
00:02:11,678 --> 00:02:13,388
And it will get there,

52
00:02:13,471 --> 00:02:16,975
but after the Jedi have run
an analysis on it first.

53
00:02:17,058 --> 00:02:21,771
I protest. I must personally deliver
the tumor to the Chancellor as ordered.

54
00:02:21,855 --> 00:02:24,399
You can protest all you want.

55
00:02:24,899 --> 00:02:26,693
My word is final.

56
00:02:33,408 --> 00:02:35,827
You have one more physical to pass.

57
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:39,581
If you are cleared,
you will be sent back to the 501 st.

58
00:02:44,419 --> 00:02:45,754
Thank you, General.

59
00:02:46,254 --> 00:02:50,091
It will be good to put this
entire incident behind you, Trooper.

60
00:02:51,801 --> 00:02:52,927
I agree.

61
00:03:12,197 --> 00:03:13,782
AZI-3!

62
00:03:14,616 --> 00:03:16,826
Hello, ARC Trooper Fives.

63
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:19,662
I regret that we were
unable to heal your friend.

64
00:03:19,746 --> 00:03:21,956
Yeah, me, too.

65
00:03:22,082 --> 00:03:24,542
Are you going to be
reprogrammed as well?

66
00:03:24,626 --> 00:03:27,587
No, AZI, I'm going back to the front.

67
00:03:27,670 --> 00:03:29,631
That is not what I heard.

68
00:03:29,714 --> 00:03:31,925
I heard your mind
was going to be wiped

69
00:03:32,008 --> 00:03:35,720
and that you would be reassigned here
and placed on sanitation detail.

70
00:03:35,804 --> 00:03:37,555
We can still be friends,

71
00:03:37,639 --> 00:03:39,432
assuming we both
remember each other

72
00:03:39,516 --> 00:03:41,393
after our memories have been erased.

73
00:03:43,478 --> 00:03:46,856
Let's go, CT-5555.

74
00:03:47,399 --> 00:03:48,400
No!

75
00:04:02,789 --> 00:04:04,416
Look what you did!

76
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:07,252
I cannot believe what you did!

77
00:04:07,335 --> 00:04:09,921
I am not getting my mind erased,
and neither are you.

78
00:04:11,381 --> 00:04:12,757
Get out of here!

79
00:04:12,841 --> 00:04:14,426
Are we escaping?

80
00:04:22,517 --> 00:04:23,726
Why are we here?

81
00:04:24,894 --> 00:04:26,271
I knew it!

82
00:04:26,354 --> 00:04:28,815
Nala Se switched the cases.

83
00:04:28,898 --> 00:04:30,358
She's trying to hide something.

84
00:04:30,984 --> 00:04:32,277
The tumor?

85
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:35,280
So we are going to
continue our research?

86
00:04:35,405 --> 00:04:38,533
Yeah, the research, that's it.
Now come on!

87
00:05:09,898 --> 00:05:13,568
I'm sorry, sir. All ships are locked down
during the emergency.

88
00:05:14,235 --> 00:05:16,196
-What about that one?
-Hey!

89
00:05:25,538 --> 00:05:27,373
There they are!

90
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,251
Sorry, brother.

91
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:50,104
I want him brought in alive!

92
00:05:50,188 --> 00:05:52,732
-Have that ship tracked.
-Yes, ma'am.

93
00:05:55,902 --> 00:05:57,111
Can you float?

94
00:05:57,195 --> 00:06:00,114
I am buoyant
and have several survival modes.

95
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:02,784
Survival, eh?

96
00:06:04,452 --> 00:06:08,248
<i>Autopilot engaged.
Navigation and orbit set.</i>

97
00:06:10,291 --> 00:06:13,628
Wait! What are you doing?
I thought we were escaping?

98
00:06:13,711 --> 00:06:15,964
Nope, this is a diversion.

99
00:06:16,047 --> 00:06:17,423
I need them to chase this pod

100
00:06:17,507 --> 00:06:20,885
while we go back and investigate
the cause of Tup's death.

101
00:06:20,969 --> 00:06:22,428
Any more questions, Doctor?

102
00:06:22,512 --> 00:06:24,764
Actually, yes, now that you mention it...

103
00:06:37,402 --> 00:06:39,404
AZI ! AZI!

104
00:06:39,487 --> 00:06:40,905
Now what?

105
00:06:40,989 --> 00:06:43,825
We're going back to figure out
why Tup died.

106
00:06:44,325 --> 00:06:46,494
I can get us there much faster.

107
00:06:52,834 --> 00:06:54,752
You're just full of surprises, aren't you?

108
00:06:54,836 --> 00:06:57,255
This is one
of my various survival modes.

109
00:06:57,338 --> 00:06:58,673
I am equipped...

110
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,093
Droids.

111
00:07:02,176 --> 00:07:04,345
A "thank you" would have been nice.

112
00:07:16,899 --> 00:07:19,611
Lord Tyranus, you summoned me?

113
00:07:19,694 --> 00:07:24,407
<i>Prime Minister Lama Su tells me
there has been a complication.</i>

114
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:27,076
<i>What has happened
to the inhibitor chip?</i>

115
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,871
It was stolen by a renegade clone.

116
00:07:29,954 --> 00:07:32,248
<i>What does this clone know?</i>

117
00:07:32,332 --> 00:07:35,918
Nothing as of yet.
He is just a soldier, after all.

118
00:07:36,002 --> 00:07:38,671
However, he was a friend

119
00:07:38,755 --> 00:07:41,132
to the clone which malfunctioned.

120
00:07:41,215 --> 00:07:43,343
<i>This behavior is unsettling.</i>

121
00:07:43,426 --> 00:07:47,680
<i>First the malfunctioning clone
and now a renegade.</i>

122
00:07:47,764 --> 00:07:52,018
<i>Are you certain these soldiers
will live up to your design in the end?</i>

123
00:07:52,101 --> 00:07:57,106
I am certain. The malfunction to
the inhibitor chip is an aberration.

124
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:59,442
<i>And how do you explain the renegade?</i>

125
00:07:59,525 --> 00:08:04,489
I'm afraid the Jedi have inspired
creative thinking in some of the clones.

126
00:08:04,572 --> 00:08:08,159
That is the cause of this type
of divergent behavior.

127
00:08:08,242 --> 00:08:12,580
<i>Will this interfere with Protocol 66?</i>

128
00:08:13,414 --> 00:08:15,500
No, I am certain of that.

129
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:18,753
<i>Find the renegade clone immediately</i>

130
00:08:18,836 --> 00:08:21,547
<i>and make sure you recover the chip.</i>

131
00:08:21,631 --> 00:08:27,011
<i>The true nature of the inhibitor chip
must not be discovered by the Jedi.</i>

132
00:08:27,095 --> 00:08:29,180
Yes, Lord Tyranus.

133
00:08:46,155 --> 00:08:47,490
What...

134
00:08:47,824 --> 00:08:51,786
Once we're inside, I need you to
get me a change of clothes, AZI.

135
00:08:59,752 --> 00:09:04,632
Trooper, I think I saw the renegade
clone head into the storage room.

136
00:09:04,716 --> 00:09:06,968
All right, let's check it out.

137
00:09:09,762 --> 00:09:11,848
I think he was over there.

138
00:09:20,022 --> 00:09:22,483
We need to get the tumor analyzed.

139
00:09:23,234 --> 00:09:24,569
Follow me.

140
00:09:31,617 --> 00:09:33,870
This is the Genetic Records Hall.

141
00:09:33,953 --> 00:09:38,249
It contains data on the original DNA
of every being we have ever cloned.

142
00:09:40,168 --> 00:09:42,003
We will compare the tumor's DNA

143
00:09:42,086 --> 00:09:44,881
versus that of Jango Fett,
the original donor.

144
00:09:44,964 --> 00:09:48,843
If any tumor like this has been
noted before, we will find it.

145
00:09:50,386 --> 00:09:52,054
The tumor, please?

146
00:09:57,393 --> 00:09:58,978
-Nothing.
-What?

147
00:09:59,061 --> 00:10:02,982
The sample doesn't match anything
found in the Jango Fett genotype.

148
00:10:03,065 --> 00:10:05,943
Furthermore, it is not
even completely organic.

149
00:10:06,027 --> 00:10:07,737
It is foreign to the body.

150
00:10:07,820 --> 00:10:09,822
Someone implanted it there.

151
00:10:09,906 --> 00:10:13,451
An implant?
You mean this isn't an accident?

152
00:10:13,534 --> 00:10:16,621
-Someone did this to Tup?
-Precisely.

153
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:24,295
There have been no unauthorized ships
leaving Kamino, General.

154
00:10:29,717 --> 00:10:32,512
I sense we are looking
in the wrong place.

155
00:10:33,221 --> 00:10:35,389
We have a report
from the Genetic Records Hall.

156
00:10:35,473 --> 00:10:36,724
Explain.

157
00:10:36,808 --> 00:10:39,519
Someone is accessing
the Jango Fett genotype.

158
00:10:39,602 --> 00:10:41,062
It's them.

159
00:10:41,145 --> 00:10:43,231
Evacuate that room quietly.

160
00:10:51,739 --> 00:10:54,784
Is there another way out of here
besides the door we came in?

161
00:10:54,867 --> 00:10:57,995
Yes, there are emergency
access hatches in every major room

162
00:10:58,079 --> 00:10:59,205
in case of flooding.

163
00:10:59,288 --> 00:11:01,791
Good, let's get moving.

164
00:11:04,669 --> 00:11:06,045
There.

165
00:11:35,116 --> 00:11:37,076
It's no good.
They've sealed it from the inside.

166
00:11:37,159 --> 00:11:41,163
Station your men at every access point
back into the main hallway system!

167
00:11:41,247 --> 00:11:42,373
Yes, ma'am.

168
00:11:45,626 --> 00:11:47,420
Did you get
all the information you needed?

169
00:11:47,503 --> 00:11:50,882
Mostly. We know that the tumor
is a foreign material

170
00:11:50,965 --> 00:11:53,342
and was implanted
for an unknown reason.

171
00:11:53,426 --> 00:11:56,679
However, there is still so much
we do not know about it.

172
00:11:56,762 --> 00:12:00,600
For example, at what stage
was it introduced to Clone Tup?

173
00:12:00,683 --> 00:12:01,976
And why?

174
00:12:02,643 --> 00:12:06,063
What is this thing?
Why would someone put it in Tup?

175
00:12:06,147 --> 00:12:09,650
I believe this is an organic chip
built out of cells.

176
00:12:10,151 --> 00:12:12,695
-What's it for?
-I do not know.

177
00:12:20,036 --> 00:12:24,165
Thanks. I need to find out
if what was in Tup's head is in mine.

178
00:12:24,248 --> 00:12:25,708
We have already done a scan and...

179
00:12:25,791 --> 00:12:29,253
But it was missed in Tup, and it
could have been missed in me, too!

180
00:12:29,337 --> 00:12:31,172
You have to take it out.

181
00:12:31,714 --> 00:12:35,009
We cannot be 100% sure
if the chip is even there.

182
00:12:35,092 --> 00:12:37,428
I know it's there.

183
00:12:37,511 --> 00:12:39,597
It is a dangerous surgery...

184
00:12:42,350 --> 00:12:45,728
Look, you got it out of Tup,
you can get it out of me.

185
00:12:45,811 --> 00:12:49,023
He died after I removed the chip.

186
00:12:49,106 --> 00:12:50,900
Maybe it is connected.

187
00:12:51,525 --> 00:12:53,361
You may die, too.

188
00:12:54,362 --> 00:12:57,114
It's a chance I have to take.

189
00:12:57,198 --> 00:12:58,699
I trust you.

190
00:13:00,660 --> 00:13:03,537
All right, I will do it.

191
00:13:03,621 --> 00:13:06,040
Let us go to a sterile facility.

192
00:13:25,977 --> 00:13:28,729
Hold still. This will not hurt a bit.

193
00:13:31,983 --> 00:13:34,318
You sure you know
what you're doing, right?

194
00:13:34,402 --> 00:13:36,988
Why, yes. I have been programmed
to perform over 100...

195
00:13:37,071 --> 00:13:38,489
All right, all right.

196
00:13:38,572 --> 00:13:39,824
Let's do this.

197
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:51,877
You will only be unconscious
for a few minutes.

198
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:20,031
There's no sign of them, General.

199
00:14:20,114 --> 00:14:21,907
They must have escaped by now.

200
00:14:21,991 --> 00:14:24,118
Escape was never their intention.

201
00:14:24,201 --> 00:14:26,203
They are investigating, searching.

202
00:14:26,287 --> 00:14:29,040
Their appearance
in the genetics labs proves this.

203
00:14:29,123 --> 00:14:31,542
But what are they searching for?

204
00:14:40,426 --> 00:14:42,887
Well? Was it...

205
00:14:43,471 --> 00:14:45,639
-Was it there?
-Yes.

206
00:14:45,931 --> 00:14:47,516
Identical in structure.

207
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:52,146
However, it appears that the one I found
in your friend had malfunctioned,

208
00:14:52,229 --> 00:14:54,398
while yours is perfectly intact.

209
00:14:56,275 --> 00:14:59,695
Are you sure
his breakdown was isolated?

210
00:15:00,071 --> 00:15:02,114
There is no way of knowing that.

211
00:15:02,990 --> 00:15:05,159
And now that we have
removed your chip,

212
00:15:05,242 --> 00:15:07,661
we do not know what will happen to you.

213
00:15:08,329 --> 00:15:10,122
So, then,

214
00:15:10,706 --> 00:15:12,333
I could snap, too?

215
00:15:12,416 --> 00:15:16,337
Possibly. But when we removed
the chip from Tup, he...

216
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:19,298
I am afraid you may die as well.

217
00:15:19,381 --> 00:15:22,593
I need to know if more clones
than just Tup and I have these,

218
00:15:22,676 --> 00:15:24,637
and when we were implanted with them.

219
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:27,389
My analysis suggests
implantation took place

220
00:15:27,473 --> 00:15:29,642
at the earliest stage of development,

221
00:15:29,725 --> 00:15:32,770
most likely when you
and Tup were only embryos.

222
00:15:33,646 --> 00:15:35,815
Then we have to start there.

223
00:15:51,288 --> 00:15:52,498
Great.

224
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:55,709
Try to act normal.

225
00:15:56,335 --> 00:15:57,753
Normal?

226
00:16:03,050 --> 00:16:04,510
Hello!

227
00:16:05,761 --> 00:16:07,763
How was that? Was that normal?

228
00:16:07,847 --> 00:16:10,558
For you, AZI, yeah.

229
00:16:39,503 --> 00:16:42,882
We will start with the earliest stage
of development.

230
00:16:56,854 --> 00:17:00,107
Nothing. I will now try
a Stage 3 embryo.

231
00:17:05,362 --> 00:17:08,032
-There it is!
-Try another.

232
00:17:12,953 --> 00:17:17,124
Based on this data, I can calculate
how many in this tree are altered.

233
00:17:23,464 --> 00:17:25,466
I can't believe it.

234
00:17:25,549 --> 00:17:27,343
They all have one.

235
00:17:32,056 --> 00:17:33,641
Don't move.

236
00:17:33,933 --> 00:17:35,851
Why are you doing this?

237
00:17:35,935 --> 00:17:38,145
I know what you've done!

238
00:17:38,562 --> 00:17:40,981
What is it that you think I have done?

239
00:17:43,317 --> 00:17:45,653
How do you explain this?

240
00:17:45,736 --> 00:17:48,072
That is a structural inhibitor chip,

241
00:17:48,155 --> 00:17:50,783
which is supposed to prevent you
from being aggressive,

242
00:17:50,866 --> 00:17:53,202
like your source, Jango Fett.

243
00:17:53,285 --> 00:17:58,749
Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas instructed us to
implant them during your growth cycle.

244
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,251
The Jedi?

245
00:18:00,334 --> 00:18:02,586
The Jedi had this done to us?

246
00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:06,715
It is not uncommon to have
inhibitors placed in a clone.

247
00:18:06,799 --> 00:18:10,761
I have analyzed this one,
and apparently it has failed.

248
00:18:10,844 --> 00:18:13,973
Up until this point,
there has never been a problem.

249
00:18:14,056 --> 00:18:16,433
Well, you have got a big problem now.

250
00:18:16,517 --> 00:18:18,018
Don't move!

251
00:18:22,898 --> 00:18:24,483
Drop your weapon.

252
00:18:24,566 --> 00:18:26,527
Master Jedi, I know what's going on.

253
00:18:26,610 --> 00:18:28,028
I have the evidence.

254
00:18:28,112 --> 00:18:32,408
The Jedi instructed that inhibitor chips
be implanted in us at birth,

255
00:18:32,491 --> 00:18:35,953
but Tup's malfunctioned.
That's what made him lose control.

256
00:18:36,412 --> 00:18:38,205
Where is the evidence?

257
00:18:38,289 --> 00:18:40,124
I have it right here.

258
00:18:40,207 --> 00:18:44,420
As you can see, the chip taken from
Clone Trooper Tup is black and rotting,

259
00:18:44,503 --> 00:18:46,422
indicating a malfunction of some sort.

260
00:18:47,089 --> 00:18:49,008
What caused the malfunction?

261
00:18:49,091 --> 00:18:52,469
It doesn't matter.
The fact is Tup's chip malfunctioned

262
00:18:52,553 --> 00:18:53,929
and it drove him insane.

263
00:18:54,013 --> 00:18:56,015
These chips have to be removed,

264
00:18:56,098 --> 00:18:59,727
otherwise the entire Republic Army
could be compromised.

265
00:18:59,810 --> 00:19:01,645
There's no proof of that!

266
00:19:01,729 --> 00:19:03,605
This is an isolated incident.

267
00:19:03,689 --> 00:19:07,484
Besides, when you removed
Trooper Tup's chip, he died.

268
00:19:07,568 --> 00:19:10,112
Well, that's not going to happen
to the rest of us.

269
00:19:10,195 --> 00:19:11,822
And how do you know that?

270
00:19:11,905 --> 00:19:13,907
Because I removed mine!

271
00:19:14,408 --> 00:19:16,410
Here is Clone Trooper Fives' chip.

272
00:19:16,493 --> 00:19:20,748
As you can see, there is no sign of
malfunction in either him or the chip.

273
00:19:20,831 --> 00:19:23,625
By removing your chip, you are a threat.

274
00:19:23,709 --> 00:19:27,046
Master Jedi, we must terminate
this trooper immediately.

275
00:19:27,129 --> 00:19:30,841
I am not a piece of hardware!
I'm a living being.

276
00:19:30,924 --> 00:19:35,179
You were created in our laboratories.
You are Kaminoan property!

277
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:40,684
Correction, technically,
he is property of the Republic.

278
00:19:40,768 --> 00:19:45,689
That does not change the fact that
he is a danger and must be terminated.

279
00:19:45,773 --> 00:19:48,442
I believe that's for me to decide.

280
00:19:48,525 --> 00:19:51,362
Fives, you are coming
with me to Coruscant.

281
00:19:51,445 --> 00:19:54,698
I think it's time you told
your story to the Chancellor.

282
00:19:54,782 --> 00:19:58,285
Master Jedi ! I beg you to reconsider!

283
00:19:58,577 --> 00:20:02,414
The Chancellor wanted all the data
on Tup to be sent to Coruscant.

284
00:20:02,498 --> 00:20:06,668
We're sending the data, the tumor
and Fives along with it.

285
00:20:06,752 --> 00:20:08,712
Then I am going with you.

286
00:20:08,796 --> 00:20:11,131
As you wish, Doctor.

287
00:20:21,016 --> 00:20:23,852
Thank you for believing in me, General.

288
00:20:24,478 --> 00:20:27,106
It is not a matter of belief, Fives,

289
00:20:27,189 --> 00:20:29,733
it is simply the right thing to do.

290
00:20:33,153 --> 00:20:35,197
It looks like you got what you wanted.

291
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,740
Thanks to you.

292
00:20:37,408 --> 00:20:39,493
I'll see you on the other side.

293
00:20:39,576 --> 00:20:41,453
The other side of what?

294
00:20:44,832 --> 00:20:45,916
Droids.

295
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:50,940
http://hiqve.com/

